This is the value of crypto currently deposited to this smart contract. Contracts with lower AUC are more likely to experience high utilization, and therefore delayed withdrawals.

This is the minimum collateral that borrowers must deposit in order to borrow. For example, if collateral is 1.5x, a borrower must deposit at least 1.5 ETH in order to borrow 1 ETH. The higher the collateral, the greater the cushion against drops in crypto prices.

This is the percentage of crypto that has already been loaned out. In the event that many lenders are trying to withdraw at the same time, contracts with high utilization may have insufficient crypto to fulfill all withdrawal requests.
